genresAdvancedInfo.name: euphonium
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A brass instrument that is similar in appearance and sound to the baritone horn. It is often used in concert bands and orchestras, and is known for its rich, mellow tone. Euphonium players are highly skilled musicians who are able to produce a wide range of dynamic and expressive sounds.
